We built a CT scanner that does not rotate the gantry as in conventional designs. Instead, the patient lies on a rotating table-literally a sheet that turns-while the X-ray tube and detector remain fixed in place.
Although this setup limits the viewing angle compared to traditional systems, it still produces good-quality images.

Several years ago, we undertook an innovative project and received some news coverage about it. We built a CT scanner that does not rotate the gantry as in conventional designs. Instead, the patient lies on a rotating table-literally a sheet that turns-while the X-ray tube and detector remain fixed in place.
